<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>HEAT VENTILATION AIR CONDITIONING (HVAC), Orifice Tube System, Pre-March 2007 - 3200, 4100, 4200, 4300,
        4400, 7300, 7400, 7500, 7600, 7700, 8500, 8600 - REMOVE AND INSTALL - COWL DRAIN TRAY/HVAC AIR INLET
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl1602505" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>COWL DRAIN TRAY/HVAC AIR INLET</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The cowl drain tray exists in several variations. The following procedures are for a typical
                        medium duty installation. If your cowl drain tray appears significantly different, refer to the
                        CAB Section in Group 16 of the Master Service Manual for procedures covering all cowl drain
                        trays.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Refer to
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f1602520">Figure 21</hotlnk>
                        while performing the following Remove and Install procedures.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove both windshield wipers.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove radio antenna wand.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect windshield washer hose (3) from bottom of cowl tray (1).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove one mounting screw (7) from the center, inside of the cowl tray.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove two mounting screws (4) securing the cowl tray air inlet to the evaporator
                    housing (8).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove two mounting bolts (2) securing the ends of the cowl tray to the cowl.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Carefully remove the cowl tray (1) by lifting it off of the windshield wiper shafts.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1602520" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg16/G1602520.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                         scalefitheight="472px"/>
                <caption>Figure 21. Cowl Drain Tray/HVAC Air Inlet (Medium Duty Shown)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. COWL TRAY</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. COWL TRAY MOUNTING NUTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. WASHER HOSE</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. MOUNTING SCREWS (TRAY TO EVAPORATOR HOUSING)</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. ANTENNA SEAL</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. AIR INLET GRILLE</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. CENTER MOUNTING SCREW</callout1>
                    <callout1>8. EVAPORATOR HOUSING</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Install</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lower the tray into position so that the windshield wiper shafts protrude through their
                    holes.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Secure the cowl tray (1) to the cowl using a mounting bolt (2) at each end of the cowl
                    tray.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install two mounting screws (4) securing the cowl tray air inlet to the evaporator
                    housing.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install one mounting screw (7) at the center, inside of the cowl tray.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect windshield washer hose (3) to bottom of cowl tray.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install radio antenna wand.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install both windshield wipers.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
